---
/**
 * rest-api · 0008 · Figure 3 — "Authorization Code + PKCE" flow.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source lesson. References the source's shared arrow
 * markers (#arw, #arwA, #arwG); they're inlined here in this figure's own <defs>
 * with the SAME ids/fills so the component renders self-contained and identical.
 * See Fig1.astro for the rationale.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="User authorizes at the authorization server, the client receives a code, exchanges it with a PKCE verifier for an access token, then calls the resource server which validates the token"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path>
            </marker>
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path>
            </marker>
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path>
            </marker>
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="16"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">AUTHORIZATION CODE + PKCE</text
            >
            <rect
                x="12"
                y="34"
                width="120"
                height="46"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text x="72" y="55" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >User</text
            >
            <text x="72" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >resource owner</text
            >
            <rect x="12" y="150" width="120" height="46" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"></rect>
            <text x="72" y="171" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700">Client</text>
            <text x="72" y="186" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >SPA / mobile app</text
            >
            <rect
                x="360"
                y="34"
                width="160"
                height="46"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef2f5"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="440"
                y="55"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">Authorization Server</text
            >
            <text x="440" y="70" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >login + consent · mints tokens</text
            >
            <rect
                x="360"
                y="150"
                width="160"
                height="46"
                rx="9"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="440"
                y="171"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">Resource Server</text
            >
            <text x="440" y="186" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >the API · validates token</text
            >
            <!-- 1 user -> AS : authorize w/ code_challenge -->
            <path
                d="M132 50 C 240 40, 300 42, 358 50"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#6b675f"
                marker-end="url(#arw)"></path>
            <text x="245" y="33" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >① authorize · sends code_challenge (PKCE)</text
            >
            <!-- 2 AS -> client : code -->
            <path
                d="M400 80 C 360 110, 180 120, 132 158"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                marker-end="url(#arw)"></path>
            <text x="248" y="116" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >② redirect back with auth code</text
            >
            <!-- 3 client -> AS : code + verifier -->
            <path
                d="M132 178 C 230 200, 320 130, 372 84"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></path>
            <text x="270" y="205" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >③ exchange code + code_verifier →</text
            >
            <!-- 4 AS -> client : access token -->
            <path
                d="M372 72 C 320 100, 230 160, 134 172"
                fill="none"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                marker-end="url(#arwG)"></path>
            <text x="300" y="150" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >④ access token (+ refresh)</text
            >
            <!-- 5 client -> RS : Bearer -->
            <line x1="132" y1="186" x2="358" y2="178" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <text x="245" y="232" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >⑤ call API · Authorization: Bearer &lt;token&gt;</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        PKCE binds the auth code to the requester, so an intercepted code is useless — it protects
        <em>public</em> clients that can't keep a secret. Authorization Code + PKCE supersedes the deprecated
        Implicit grant even for SPAs.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
